  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving Protection and WASH assistance to vulnerable communities affected by displacement. This UNICEF project provides mental health and psychosocial support, child protection services, GBV response and prevention, and access to safe water and sanitary facilities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 30,000 people, including 6,600 women, 5,400 men, 18,000 children, and 484 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
